<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="252" pageId="12" pageNumber="251" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1779,2020]" pageId="12" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1852,1876]" pageId="12" pageNumber="251">Remarks:</emphasis>
Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyatake" authorityYear="1970" box="[393,575,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metasternalis">
<emphasis box="[393,575,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="251">P. metasternalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giorgi &amp; Vandenberg" authorityYear="2012" box="[637,759,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kashaya">
<emphasis box="[637,759,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="251">P. kashaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been confused with this species in the past (see the corresponding remarks sections, above). 
<taxonomicName box="[618,906,1888,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctifrons">
<emphasis box="[618,906,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="251">Phaenochilus punctifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from both of these other species by the less expansive pronotum with the lateral part on each side of the head only weakly prolonged and tightly, evenly rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[532,622,1960,1984]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[397,1195,186,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-58@10.[354,1232,185,1955]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Frontal views of Phaenochilus species, males (for comparative purposes, size adjusted to constant head width using outer margin of eyes as a landmark). 25, P. punctifrons Weise; 26, P. metasternalis Miyatake; 27, P.kashaya, n. sp." pageId="12" pageNumber="251">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[637,713,1960,1984]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1329,1352]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,943,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-505@11.[151,1436,941,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Pronota of Phaenochilus species (size adjusted to constant head width using outer margin of eyes as a landmark): 28, overlapping outlines of all three of the species shown separately at right; 29, P. punctifrons Weise; 30, P. metasternalis Miyatake; 31, P. kashaya n. sp." pageId="12" pageNumber="251">28, 29</figureCitation>
), by the roughly semicircular shape of the elytral dorsum in a frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[302,386,1996,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[397,1195,186,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-58@10.[354,1232,185,1955]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Frontal views of Phaenochilus species, males (for comparative purposes, size adjusted to constant head width using outer margin of eyes as a landmark). 25, P. punctifrons Weise; 26, P. metasternalis Miyatake; 27, P.kashaya, n. sp." pageId="12" pageNumber="251">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), and by the nearly symmetrical basal lobe of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1210,1996,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,185,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-134@6.[151,1436,185,1852]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Male genitalia of Phaenochilus species. 8, P. mikado Weise (redrawn from Kamiya 1959, Sasaji 1971): a, ventral view of phallobase; b, left lateral view of phallobase; c, left lateral view of sipho. 9, P. flaviceps Miyatake: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (reproduced from Miyatake 1970b). 10, P. indicus Miyatake: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (reproduced from Miyatake 1970b). 11, P. punctifrons Weise: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (specimen from Surigao, Mindanao). Scale bar applies to figs 9–11." pageId="12" pageNumber="251">Fig. 11a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="252">
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[444,597,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctifrons">
<emphasis box="[444,597,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="252">P. punctifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chapin, E. A." box="[819,995,151,175]" pageId="13" pageNumber="252" pagination="227 - 271" refId="ref9928" refString="Chapin, E. A. (1965 b) The genera of the Chilocorini (Coleoptera, Coccinellidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 133 (4), 227 - 271." type="journal article" year="1965">Chapin (1965b)</bibRefCitation>
based on an individual from Mindanao Island which he recorded as “Mindanao, Kolambugan, C.F.Baker #16609” in his little black notebook, and designated as “X-14” (see also remarks under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyatake" authorityYear="1970" box="[672,851,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metasternalis">
<emphasis box="[672,851,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="252">P. metasternalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, above). This slide could not be located in Chapin’s slide cabinet (USNM), but a second specimen from Mindanao Island labeled “Surigao, Mindanao, Baker” was dissected and found to have matching male genitalia except for the shape of the sipho. When we transferred our new dissection between media of different viscosities, the sipho temporarily assumed an S-shape matching Chapin’s drawing, apparently due to a difference in the hydrostatic pressure on the outside and inside of the siphonal tube. When allowed to equilibrate, the structure resumes the simple curved shape seen in our figure (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,185,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-134@6.[151,1436,185,1852]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Male genitalia of Phaenochilus species. 8, P. mikado Weise (redrawn from Kamiya 1959, Sasaji 1971): a, ventral view of phallobase; b, left lateral view of phallobase; c, left lateral view of sipho. 9, P. flaviceps Miyatake: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (reproduced from Miyatake 1970b). 10, P. indicus Miyatake: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (reproduced from Miyatake 1970b). 11, P. punctifrons Weise: a, ventral view of phallobase; b, right lateral view of phallobase; c, right lateral view of sipho (specimen from Surigao, Mindanao). Scale bar applies to figs 9–11." pageId="13" pageNumber="252">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). (See also “Remarks” section for 
<taxonomicName box="[580,744,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Phaenochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monostigma">
<emphasis box="[580,744,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="252">P. monostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, above.)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
